External morphology (Fig. 17
A-C
). Body relatively wide. Foot and tail moderate, anterior foot corners relatively short. Rhinophores similar in size to oral tentacles, slightly wrinkled, robust. Dorsal cerata fusiform, long, continuously attached to rudimentary but uninterrupted notal edge without forming clusters. Apices of cerata pointed. Notum narrow but distinct throughout both lateral sides of body. Digestive gland diverticulum fills significant volume of cerata. Anal opening on right side below notal edge in first half of body but closer to middle. Reproductive openings lateral, below notal edge around middle part of body.

Jaws (Fig. 17
D-F
). Masticatory process more than one-third as long as jaw body. Edge of masticatory processes bears ca. 20 denticles that continue to form several reduced rows of denticles on body of masticatory processes.
